<h1 id="a-list-of-health-and-safety-resources-for-rit-students">A List of Health and Safety Resources for RIT Students</h1>

<h3 id="things-to-do-before-returning-to-campus">Things to Do Before Returning to Campus</h3>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://mylife.rit.edu/StarRezPortalX/99AE77D5/10/724/Online_Forms-Location_Returning_F">Complete travel form by July 24, 2020</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://coronavirus.health.ny.gov/find-test-site-near-you">Get tested and be able to provide proof of a negative test</a></li>
  <li>Quarantine 2 weeks before traveling to RITâ€™s campus</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="while-on-campus">While On Campus</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Wear a mask <strong>at all times</strong> in RIT facilities and even while physically distancing</li>
  <li>Practice good hygiene - washing hands for 30s, disinfecting personal space in classrooms, labs, and covering coughs and sneezes</li>
  <li>Please stay home if you're feeling sick or have any of <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/symptoms-testing/symptoms.html">these symptoms</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://dailyhealth.rit.edu/assessment">Complete the Daily Health Survey everyday for both on and off campus residence</a> (<a href="https://www.rit.edu/news/rit-launches-daily-health-screen-monitoring-covid-19-symptoms">How to use</a>)</li>
  <li>Use the Location Check In for Contact Tracing (Link available soon)</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.rit.edu/fa/parking/transportation/bus">Bus Schedules</a></li>
</ul>

